  "texts": [
    "Retrieval Augmented Prompting (RAP) fetches relevant information from a knowledge base in real-time and integrates it into the input prompt 57, 72.",
    "In contrast to the other prompting techniques, using RAP, the model generates responses by relying not only on its internal knowledge but also on external information, which might mitigate hallucination.",
    "However, its implementation is more complex and introduces dependencies on external data sources.",
    "In our study, the knowledge base includes 125 documents (such as articles, books, and guidelines) recommended by the Academy of Nutrition and Dietetics 42, as references for the RD exam.",
    "The full list of the references used for RAP is provided in Supplementary Table S.7."
  ],
